The bundled noble-curves-and-hashes.mjs file contains code from:

  @noble/curves  (https://github.com/paulmillr/noble-curves)
  @noble/hashes  (https://github.com/paulmillr/noble-hashes)

Both are MIT licensed by Paul Miller (paulmillr.com).

Bundle composition (Arpass v5 requirements):
  - p256 (NIST P-256 / secp256r1) ECDSA
  - sha256
  - hkdf (RFC 5869)
  - hmac
  - mod (modular arithmetic)

The bundle was produced with esbuild, format=esm, target=es2022.
Source entry:

  export { p256 } from '@noble/curves/nist.js';
  export { sha256 } from '@noble/hashes/sha2.js';
  export { hkdf } from '@noble/hashes/hkdf.js';
  export { hmac } from '@noble/hashes/hmac.js';
  export { mod } from '@noble/curves/abstract/modular.js';

